author: Fiona Flynn
title: TV | The Sex Change Spitfire Ace
text: Quite the programme title 'ey? This documentary tells the story of the unique relationship between two of the most remarkable pioneers of the 20th century - Michael Dillon, the world's first woman to transition to a man, and Roberta Cowell, Britain's first man to become a woman. Both sex changes caused a press sensation in the 1950s, but ultimately ended in tragedy, and this programme includes previously unseen correspondence between Roberta and Michael, discovered by journalist Liz Hodgkinson, which reveals a sensational twist in this extraordinary story.
